The key issues for which forests provide benefits in Idaho were:        1. Potential benefit to wildlife and biodiversity,       2. Potential benefit to water quality and quantity,       3. Potential benefit to air quality, and       4. Potential benefit to sustainable forest based markets.   The scores for all cells are then stratified into five classes using natural breaks. This composite benefits map identifies the areas with the least benefit through those with the greatest benefits as identified in the issues and sub-issues used in the assessment.  Idaho Statewide Assessment of Forest Resources document contains additional information and can be found at: http://www.idl.idaho.gov/bureau/ForestAssist/safr/final/061410-ID-SAFR-FINAL.pdf.</abstract><purpose>Summarize the benefits of forests.</purpose><supplinf>http://www.idl.idaho.gov/bureau/ForestAssist/safr/safr-final.html</supplinf><langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata></descript><timeperd><timeinfo><sngdate><caldate>20090921</caldate></sngdate></timeinfo><current>publication date</current></timeperd><status><progress>Complete</progress><update>As needed</update></status><spdom><bounding><westbc> -117.529688</westbc><eastbc> -110.655391</eastbc><northbc> 49.035609</northbc><southbc> 41.956776</southbc></bounding><lboundng><leftbc Sync="TRUE">2241757.098209</leftbc><rightbc Sync="TRUE">2744677.098209</rightbc><bottombc Sync="TRUE">1199898.094443</bottombc><topbc Sync="TRUE">1981638.094443</topbc></lboundng></spdom><keywords><theme><themekt>ESRI Geography Network Thesaurus</themekt><themekey>Benefits to Forest Health</themekey><themekey>State Assessment of Forest Resources</themekey><themekey>SAFR</themekey><themekey>State Assessment</themekey><themekey>Statewide Forest Resource Strategy</themekey><themekey>SFRS</themekey></theme><place><placekt>None</placekt><placekey>Idaho</placekey></place></keywords><accconst>Public, Federal Goverment, Idaho State Government, IDL Authorized Users</accconst><useconst>None.
